    "body": "Maybe @peterbitfly could help how to reduce uncles based on his experience.\r\n\r\nIf you are running remote miners, you could try running Geth with `--miner.noverify`. Originally external miners submitted possible solutions to Geth, which double checked them before pushing to the network. If you feel confident your miner nodes produce good PoWs, you can tell Geth to skip double checking .This can shave off some milliseconds from network propagation.",
